# Power Automate CLI Configuration
#
# This CLI uses shared configuration from the Microsoft-Dataverse-CLI project.
# You must first clone and configure the dataverse-cli:
# https://github.com/adbertram/Microsoft-Dataverse-CLI
#
# The powerautomate CLI will automatically look for configuration in the
# dataverse-cli directory (relative path: ../Microsoft-Dataverse-CLI/.env)
#
# Required variables (set in dataverse-cli .env):
#   - DATAVERSE_CLIENT_ID (Azure AD app registration)
#   - DATAVERSE_TENANT_ID (Azure AD tenant)
#   - DATAVERSE_ENVIRONMENT_ID (Power Platform environment, e.g., Default-<tenant-id>)
#
# Authentication:
# The Power Automate Management API requires delegated (user) authentication.
# When you run commands, you'll be prompted to authenticate interactively via
# device code flow - no username/password needed in the config!
#
# The CLI will display a URL and code. Open the URL in your browser, enter the
# code, and complete authentication. Your session will be cached for future use.
#
# See dataverse-cli documentation for complete configuration options:
# https://github.com/adbertram/Microsoft-Dataverse-CLI#configuration
